&quot; Denial is a luxury you choose for yourself. Enjoy your wine, High Elf. It is your &quot;right&quot; to dream.&quot;<br>
Daon pauses for a brief moment, then speaks again in his distant, deep voice.<br>
&quot;As it is my &quot;right&quot;... to destroy your dreams. All things die, even High Elf hopes.&quot;<br>
<br>
Daon fades away in a swirl of magic. The corpse of a patron now revealed, slumped in the corner. The body was hidden by Daon sitting in the chair, as the Necromancer sat to rest. The body is shriveled, as if all the life was drained. The dead eyes staring at the ceiling. Dead eyes that almost seemed pleading.<br>
